We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
Revise the Notes to Financial Statements to effect the recommendations stated in Column four of the Table 1;
Round-off the figures in the narrative description into thousands for consistency of presentation in the tables and in the notes;

We recommended that management:

Demand from the contractor the immediate completion of the construction of the project; 


Refrain from approving extension of project completion without concrete valid reason; 



Direct the MEO to take overall considerations that will be needed in making plans for the projects; and



Require the contractor to pay liquidated damages. If the contractor has not been paid the remaining contract price, deduct the liquidated damages from such amount.

