We recommended that management:
 (a) maintain special accounts for each economic enterprises in the Gen Fund;
(b) operate and manage the corporate economic enterprise separate and distinct from purely government/public functions;
(c ) segregate the assets, liabilities and equity of the economic enterprises from the General Fund proper;
(d) manage these assets to derive profits as additional source of revenue;
(e) identify and maintain appropriate property subsidiary ledger cards;
and (f) prepare the financial reports for each of the economic enterprise.

We recommended that management:
(a) furnish the auditor copies of delivery receipts, purchase orders and certificate of acceptance, together with all supporting documents, within the time or period; 
and (b) observe the proper accomplishment of all entries in the purchase orders (PO) in accordance with COA Circular No. 96-010.
